<HEADLINE>
Japanese troops to help rescue work in Indonesia
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
TOKYO, Jan 4
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japan on Tuesday put its army, air force 
and navy on standby to provide assistance to survivors of Asia's 
tsunami disaster, with most of their work expected to be in 
worst-hit Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
An advance team comprising some 20 personnel will leave Japan 
later Tuesday to visit Indonesia, Thailand and Malaysia to collect 
first-hand information on what the reo sent nearly 120 civilian emergency workers to 
tsunami-hit countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
